Package au.com.innodev.wmboost.data

Contains classes that make it easier to access and manipulate webMethods documents.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BaseUnitEntry
    Base interface for references to unit entries, which are the most common type of entries.
    CollectionEntry<E>
    A reference to a unit entry where the value is a collection.
    DirectIDataFactory
    Factory for the creation of IData instances.
    Document
    Represents a document that contains key/value entries, as an abstraction of webMethods' IData.
    DocumentFactory
    Provides factory methods for the creation of Document instances.
    EntryIterableResource
    An iterable for document entries that is also exposed as a resource (i.e., a Closeable).
    HasKey
    An interface for entries, which have a key.
    ItemEntry<T>
    A reference to a unit entry where the value is a single item.
    KeyValue
    A key/value pair corresponding to a document entry
    NestedDocEntry
    A reference to an entry with a nested document as the value.
    SplitEntry<E>
    Allows access and modification of a group of entries that share the same key.
    StringEntry
    A reference to an entry with a string as the value.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DocumentFactoryBuilder
    Builds a DocumentFactory.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    NullValHandling
    Specifies the behaviour when an entry contains a null value.
    RemoveEntryOption
    Strictness option for removing entries.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EntryAccessException
    An exception that occurs when accessing document entries
    InexistentEntryException
    Exception thrown when the document didn't contain an expected entry
    UnexpectedEntryValueException
    Exception thrown when the entry contained a value that was unexpected.

Package au.com.innodev.wmboost.data Description

Contains classes that make it easier to access and manipulate webMethods documents.

It provides an abstraction on top of classes like webMethods' IData and IDataUtil. Behind the scenes, the types and structures expected by webMethods are used.
